      "role": "user",
      "content": "Confirmed. The decision for Deep Sleep Mode is a safety protocol to prevent a total battery depletion event during the Jezero Crater scan, which would result in catastrophic hardware failure and zero data return. \n\nIs there any technical reason why the scheduled spectral scan cannot be completed within the remaining 12% power window prior to the sleep cycle?",
